# Wordpress Bento-Theme #

## Installation Notes ##

### Common Bento Files ###

For local development with out an internet connection get a local version of Bento-Themes common files from http://gitorious.org/opensuse/themes and place theme into your local theme directory.
Use GIT to check out the repository: git clone git://gitorious.org/opensuse/themes.git

## Used Plugins on opensuse.org ##

In general the following WP-Plugins are currently (2010-04-15) in use:

  Brian's Threaded Comments
    By Brian Meidell
    http://meidell.dk/threadedcomments/

  Digg This
    By Aviran Mordo
    http://www.aviransplace.com/index.php/digg-this-wordpress-plugin/

  Math Comment Spam Protection
    By Michael Woehrer
    http://sw-guide.de/wordpress/plugins/math-comment-spam-protection/

  Recent Comments
    By Nick Momrik
    http://mtdewvirus.com/code/wordpress-plugins/

  StatPress
    By Daniele Lippi 
    http://www.statpress.org/

  WP-PostRatings
    By Lester 'GaMerZ' Chan 
    http://lesterchan.net/portfolio/programming/php/
  
At news.opensuse.org are additionally installes:

  Event Calendar
    By Alex Tingle 
    http://wpcal.firetree.net/

  Subscribe2
    By Matthew Robinson
    http://subscribe2.wordpress.com/
